---
import LegalLayout from '../layouts/LegalLayout.astro';
---

<LegalLayout
  title="Terms &amp; Conditions"
  description="The terms and conditions for using FreshLine Cleaning's carpet and upholstery cleaning services."
  slug="terms"
>
  <span class="last-updated">Last updated: May 2025</span>

  <div class="notice-box">
    <p>
      These terms apply to all cleaning services provided by FreshLine Cleaning. By booking a service
      with us, you agree to these terms. If you have any questions before booking, please ask us first.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2>About Us</h2>
  <p>
    FreshLine Cleaning is a local carpet and upholstery cleaning service operating in Birmingham and
    the wider West Midlands. We can be reached at
    <a href="mailto:hello@example.com">hello@example.com</a> or
    <a href="tel:+447000000000">+44 7000 000000</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>Quotes and Pricing</h2>
  <p>
    All quotes are estimates based on the information and photos you provide before your appointment.
    The final price may differ from the initial estimate in the following circumstances:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>The actual size or condition of the area is different from what was described or photographed</li>
    <li>The level of soiling, staining or damage is greater than expected</li>
    <li>Additional areas or items are requested on the day</li>
    <li>Access difficulties or parking issues result in additional time or effort</li>
    <li>A different or more specialised cleaning method is required</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    We will always discuss any pricing changes with you before carrying out additional work.
    We will never charge more without your agreement.
  </p>

  <h2>Stain Removal</h2>
  <p>
    We will always do our best to remove stains, but stain removal cannot be guaranteed.
    Some stains — particularly those that are old, set in, caused by certain chemicals, or where
    previous cleaning attempts have been made — may not be fully removable.
  </p>
  <p>
    We will advise you honestly about what results to expect before we start.
    A stain not fully responding to treatment does not entitle you to a refund if the rest of
    the service has been carried out to a satisfactory standard.
  </p>

  <h2>Access and Parking</h2>
  <p>
    You are responsible for ensuring reasonable access to your property and the areas to be cleaned.
    This includes:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Ensuring there is a clear route to the areas requiring cleaning</li>
    <li>Providing access to a standard 13-amp electrical socket</li>
    <li>Arranging or advising us of available parking near your property</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    If access or parking is not available on arrival and the appointment cannot proceed, we reserve
    the right to charge a call-out fee to cover travel costs.
  </p>

  <h2>Your Responsibilities Before the Appointment</h2>
  <p>To help us deliver the best results and protect your belongings, please ensure that:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Fragile, valuable or irreplaceable items have been removed from the areas to be cleaned</li>
    <li>Small items (toys, ornaments, cables) have been cleared from floors and furniture</li>
    <li>Pets are secured away from the work area for their safety and ours</li>
    <li>You have disclosed any known pre-existing damage to carpets, fabrics or furniture</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    We are not liable for damage to items that were not disclosed or that remained in the work area
    against our reasonable advice.
  </p>

  <h2>Drying Times</h2>
  <p>
    Drying times given are estimates only and depend on factors including room ventilation, humidity,
    carpet type and pile depth, and the method used. Most carpets are dry within 2–4 hours, but this
    cannot be guaranteed.
  </p>
  <p>
    We recommend keeping windows open and ventilating the room after cleaning to reduce drying time.
    We are not responsible for issues arising from carpets or upholstery not drying within an
    expected timeframe where reasonable precautions have been taken.
  </p>

  <h2>Cancellations and Rescheduling</h2>
  <p>
    We understand that plans change. We ask for as much notice as possible if you need to cancel
    or rearrange your appointment.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Cancellations or rescheduling with more than 24 hours' notice — no charge</li>
    <li>Cancellations or rescheduling with less than 24 hours' notice — we may charge a small fee to
        cover our time and travel costs, at our discretion</li>
    <li>No-shows (we arrive and cannot gain access) — a call-out fee may be charged</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    We will always try to be flexible and reasonable. If something unexpected has come up, just let
    us know as soon as you can.
  </p>

  <h2>Payment</h2>
  <p>
    Payment is due on completion of the work unless otherwise agreed in advance. We accept cash
    and bank transfer. We will confirm accepted payment methods when you book.
  </p>
  <p>
    For larger jobs, we may request a small deposit to secure the booking. This will be clearly
    communicated and agreed before your appointment.
  </p>

  <h2>Liability</h2>
  <p>
    We take care to provide a professional service and take reasonable precautions to avoid damage.
    However, our liability is limited as follows:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>We are not liable for pre-existing damage to carpets, upholstery or surfaces that was
        not caused by our work</li>
    <li>We are not liable for items left in the work area that were damaged as a result of not
        being removed before the clean</li>
    <li>Our liability for any claim arising from our services is limited to the amount paid
        for the specific service in question</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Nothing in these terms limits our liability for death or personal injury caused by our
    negligence, or for any other liability that cannot be excluded by law.
  </p>

  <h2>Customer Satisfaction and Complaints</h2>
  <p>
    We want you to be happy with our work. If you are not satisfied with any aspect of our service,
    please let us know as soon as possible — ideally on the day, or within 48 hours of the appointment.
  </p>
  <p>
    We will do our best to address any concerns promptly and fairly. Complaints raised significantly
    after the appointment and without reasonable justification for the delay may be more difficult
    to investigate and resolve.
  </p>

  <h2>Right to Refuse Work</h2>
  <p>
    We reserve the right to refuse or discontinue work if:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>The property or working conditions present a health or safety risk</li>
    <li>The condition of the area is materially different from what was described or photographed</li>
    <li>The customer is abusive or threatening towards our staff</li>
    <li>Items to be cleaned appear to contain hazardous materials or substances</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    In such cases, we may charge a reasonable call-out fee to cover travel and time.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes to These Terms</h2>
  <p>
    We may update these terms from time to time. The version on our website at the time of your
    booking will apply. We recommend checking this page before making a booking if you have not
    used our services recently.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact Us</h2>
  <p>If you have any questions about these terms, please contact us:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Email: <a href="mailto:hello@example.com">hello@example.com</a></li>
    <li>Phone: <a href="tel:+447000000000">+44 7000 000000</a></li>
    <li>Location: Birmingham, United Kingdom</li>
  </ul>
</LegalLayout>
